                                                                                              Examples of maintenance controls include: controlled maintenance, maintenance tools, nonlocal
                                                                                              maintenance, maintenance personnel, and timely maintenance.
                                                                                              Organizations: (i) perform periodic and timely maintenance on organizational systems; and (ii)
                                                                                              provide effective controls on the tools, techniques, mechanisms, and personnel used to conduct
                                                                                              system maintenance.
